The paper deals with an optimization problem in bipartite matching, which is a classic topic in computer science. The focus of the paper is on balancing relevance and diversity, which suggests that it may belong to the subfields of machine learning (cs.LG) or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of submodular functions as the objective function also suggests that it may belong to the subfield of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also proposes novel algorithms with provable guarantees, which suggests that it may belong to the subfield of game theory (cs.GT) or information theory (cs.IT).
